2.  Is javascript a dynamically typed language or a statically typed language ?
A.  Correct flow:
    JavaScript
     JS Code
       ↓
    Parsed + JIT compiled/interpreted by engine (like V8)
       ↓
    Runs in browser/node
       ↓
    Type checking happens while running (Runtime)
    Example:
    let a = 10;
    a = "Hello"; // allowed at runtime
    JavaScript engine checks values during execution.

    TypeScript
    TS Code
      ↓
    Compile Time Checking
      ↓
    Converted (transpiled) into JavaScript
      ↓
    JavaScript runs
    Example:
    let a: number = 10;

    Important thing:
    TypeScript does not convert directly into binary.
    It first converts into JavaScript:
    TypeScript → JavaScript → Machine-level execution






















a = "Hello"; // compile-time error

TypeScript checks types before the code runs.
